request.description:
This request allows user to login, returning the whole firebase's native login response as well as the user's detail from urvana DB.

This method implements a test in order to ad the response's access token to the environment to be available for all requests as {{userToken}} environment variable. (se headers (Authorization) in other requests for reference)

response.name: login

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description:
this method creates a user in both firebase and urvana's database if firebase's response was successful. 
If the user already exists firebase returns an error. 
Password is set here.

response.name: register

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description: this method just allows us to verify if the auth token is set correctly in the headers. execute it and the message must be "request authenticated"

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description:
This method gets all currently active users.
- active user: v_status = 1
- inactive user (softly deleted): v_status = 0

response.name: Get All Users

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description:
Get a specific maintenance fee by a monthly fee Id.

Params:

- maintenancefeeId

Example: 

{{remoteHost}}//api/v1/maintenance_fee/{{maintenancefeeId}}

{{remoteHost}}//api/v1/maintenance_fee/12

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description: Creates a maintenance fee for a given residential.

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description: Updates a maintenance fee given a maintenance fee Id.

header.value: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS

request.description:
Softs deletes a Monthly fee.

Change the status of a monthly fee so it be skipped when fetching monthly fees.

Params: 

- MonthlyFeeId
